# THIRD-PARTY-LICENSES.md

**This file is GENERATED — do not hand-edit.** It lists every third-party
Rust crate awl depends on (native + wasm targets, via the one `Cargo.lock`),
grouped by SPDX license identifier, with each license's full text.

Regenerate with:

```sh
cargo install cargo-about --locked --features cli
cargo about generate about.hbs -o THIRD-PARTY-LICENSES.md
```

`about.toml` (repo root) lists every license identifier this generation run
is configured to accept — see its own header comment for the GPL-compatibility
audit. awl's own source is GPL-3.0-only; see [`LICENSE`](./LICENSE) and
[`NOTICE`](./NOTICE). Bundled FONT and DICTIONARY assets are covered
separately (not Rust dependencies) — see
[`assets/fonts/LICENSES.md`](./assets/fonts/LICENSES.md) and
[`assets/dict/LICENSES.md`](./assets/dict/LICENSES.md). See
[`CREDITS.md`](./CREDITS.md) for the human-readable thank-you this file backs.
**Note:** `awl` itself appears once, under GPL-3.0-only, as the workspace
root crate `cargo about` walks from — that entry is awl, not a dependency.

